deck: Hsu Hao was a Mongolian warrior from the evil Red Dragon Clan. Introduced in Mortal Kombat Deadly Alliance as a traitor to Earthrealm, Hsu Hao infiltrated and successfully disabled the U.S. Special Forces only means of inter-realm travel. Thankfully, Jax caught on to this betrayal and tore out Hao's heart implant, resulting in a very painful death for the mischievous Mongolian. In the alternate timeline, he was slaughtered by Scorpion during a pursuit for Kenshi. Hsu Hao is as dead as they come now.
description:
Original Timeline

Deadly Alliance

Hsu Hao was a Red Dragon operative, that has infiltrated himself inside the Special Forces top secret Outer World Investigation Agency, led by Sonya Blade and Major Jackson Briggs. Once Mavado, his superior, gave Hsu Hao the order, Hsu Hao activated a miniature nuclear weapon inside the OIA's H.Q., and once it blew off, their underground base and their means to inter-realm travel were destroyed as well. Unbeknownst to Hao, Jax had caught on to his mischief and secretly followed him to Outworld, hungry for vengeance.

Later on, while the Red Dragon clan was working secretly for one of the halves of the Deadly Alliance (Quan Chi), Hsu Hao was ordered by Mavado to assassinate Shang Tsung. On his way to Shang Tsung's palace, he was ambushed and badly beaten to a pulp by an enraged Major Jackson Briggs. He showed the worthless traitor no mercy. Jax grabbed onto Hao's artifical chest implantation, began roughly twisting at the metal and tearing through his flesh with no mercy. Hao screamed hysterically in horrible agony as Jax laughed out loud and ripped his heart implant right out from his chest. Raiden himself narrates that this was indeed, a very painful way to go. Hsu Hao bled out right in front of Shang Tsungs's palace moments later, failing his mission and going straight to hell.

Hsu Hao's Armageddon

During the events of Mortal Kombat Armageddon, Hsu Hao was mysteriously resurrected from the dead to fight along side the Forces of Darkness in the final showdown of good and evil. It was likely Shinnok who resurrect the murdered Mongolian, since he was in charge of the Forces of Darkness.

Hsu Hao was revealed to be killed in the shockwave of Blaze's death in his own ending. He was then reincarnated in the Netherrealm as an Oni, where he would forever wonder the wastelands of hell and serve as a minion of the underworld.

Alternate Timeline

Hsu Hao is only seen at the very beginning in the first issue of Mortal Kombat X's comic tie-in. Hao appears as a squad leader of Red Dragon mercenaries, and is seen chasing after an injured Kenshi and his son, Takeda. When they finally reach the duo, Kenshi yells for his son to run away and the crew of Red Dragon pummel the blind man to a pulp. Hsu Hao was very glad to follow through on his masters orders, screaming that Daegon commanded that Kenshi be executed. He was just about to finish him off, but Scorpion came to the rescue. Scorpion threw his spear right into Hsu Hao's artificial heart implant, and pulled him towards himself with all of his might. The mischievous Mongolian was then forcefully dragged across the woods until his face finally collided with Scorpion's fist, punching straight through his head. Chunks of brain matter and bone were sent flying through the back of his skull, even Hao's eyeballs were pushed out through the new gaping hole in his noggin. Hsu Hao will not return again.

Trivia

Hsu Hao is quite an infamous character in the Mortal Kombat franchise. Not only is he despised by players everywhere, he is even hated by the developers themselves. John Vogel had said he wrote Jax's ending because he wanted to get rid of Hsu Hao and had no intentions of bringing him back. He wanted to get rid of this joke in the most sadistic way possible, and Vogel was all to happy to make him die in such a gruesome manner. However, due to the development of Armaggedon, which was going to have every character from MK, he had no choice but to bring him back to the roster, much to his dismay.

Now, Hsu Hao will never return again as he was now killed by Scorpion. Ironically Hsu Hao is Ed Boon's least favorite character with Scorpion being his most loved. Ed Boon had vocally voiced his hatred for Hsu Hao in several interviews, pleased about the unpleasant passing of Hao. When the alternate timeline story was launched in Mortal Kombat 9, Boon let fans know Hao would not be playable ever again, but did like Scorpion, so many came to the conclusion that Hsu Hao might be killed again by the yellow ninja himself when Mortal Kombat X was announced. The fan service was delivered, and Hao was brained like he should've been at birth in the very first issue of the Mortal Kombat X prequel comic book, not even making it to the actual game itself.
name: Hsu Hao

deck: Ventolin Xtal is the young queen of an alien planet known as Mer'z'bow that fell in love with Bucky Barnes.
description:
Origin

Ventolin Xtal is the queen of the planet known as Mer’z’bow and lead a race of peace-minded creatures. She had ruled the world for a long period of time and her subject where very loyal to her.

Creation

Ventolin Xtal was created by Ales Kot and Marco Rudy and first appeared in Bucky Barnes: The Winter Soldier issue 3 (2015).

Major Story Arcs

Queen falls in Love

The quite life Ventolin Xtal led soon was desturbed when creatures from outer space appeared on her planet, Bucky Barnes and Daisy Louise Johnson (Quake). The two where send on a mission to kill Ventolin, because of a future vision that seemed to predict that if Ventolin Xtal remained alive, would lead unto a terrible intergalactic war. It was however when Bucky tried to infiltrate the lair of the queen, that the two met and almost instantly fell in love with one another. Forsaking his mission to kill her and instead find another way to stop the future events, Bucky worked together with Ventolin. It was however then that an enemy named Crossbones (Barnes) set it's target on both Ventolin and Bucky, for as of yet unknown reasons.

description:
Mortal Kombat X

Suchin is mentioned by Kenshi when talking to Hanzo Hasashi. He mentions that all began when a cover mission to kill the Red Dragon's leader, Daegon, has failed when his cover was blown. Sonya then called him to say that the Red Dragon sent a message, claiming that he had a son, Takeda, living in Thailand.

While Kenshi raced to Thailand, Suchin sent Takeda to other city, and later she dealt with the Red Dragon herself. She took down the three soldiers who arrived at her house, but unfortunately as she killed the last one of them, that one would also shoot a bullet through her chest, killing her instantly. Kenshi arrives at the scene and sees her body, and later he recovers Takeda safe and sound.

deck: The Robin or Bucky to the Guardian of the Republic. There have been a few 'Mariannes' throughout history. Personally trained by the Guardians themsevles.
description:
Not every Guardian of the Republic seems to have had a 'Marianne' backing them up, but the most prolific one before Alima seemed to be a young Parisian named Jeanne who aided that era's Guardian (Marc Saint-Clair) amidst the Nazi-occupation of France in World War II.

The latest woman to be chosen is young Alima Berzaim, a streetwise youth who helped the current Guardian (Maxim Saint-Clair) stop a plot by the dastardly crime syndicate CRIMEN. She proved more than capable of handling herself in tight situations, and was even shown to be quite formidable, combat-wise. After aiding the stalwart hero, young Alima was chosen to be the Guardian's partner. A role she happily accepted.

deck: A Space Ghost villain who has the power to control animals with his mind.
description:
The Creature King first appeared in an episode of Space Ghost called "Creature King." He is able to control animals with the help of the special helmet that he wears.

Backstory: Although Creature King's origins are still very clouded, his origins are most likely linked to gene splicing. The Creature King is not just known for his animal control, he is also very skilled at gene manipulation. This could clear up some things about his shrouded past. If you pay attention to the the way Creature King looks you will find he has bat-like fangs and reptilian eyes, and if you look closely at the way his helmet works you will see that it emits a sonar-like beam, very similar to that of a bat. The creature King might have spliced his DNA with that of a bat and other animals to amplify his mind control abilities. The helmet might not even be the source of his powers, it could just be a way of controlling his powers' strength and frequency.

The Council of Doom: The creature King was on a team of Super-villains with the goal of destroying Space ghost. The other members were: Spider Woman(not the Marvel one of course) Metallus, Moltar, Zorak and Brak.
name: Creature King
